A RESOLUTION
1 Commending Kimberly Seals Allers and recognizing April 11, 2025, as Irth Day; and for
2 other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, Kimberly Seals Allers is an award-winning journalist, five-time author,
4 international speaker, strategist, and nationally recognized advocate for maternal and infant
5 health equity; and
6 WHEREAS, she has served as a senior editor at ESSENCE and as a writer at FORTUNE
7 magazine, lending her voice and talents to prominent platforms while addressing the racial
8 and socio-cultural complexities of birth, breast-feeding, and motherhood; and
9 WHEREAS, Kimberly Seals Allers further serves as the founder of Irth, a digital platform
10 designed as a "Yelp-like" app and aimed at addressing bias and racism in maternity and
11 infant care; and
12 WHEREAS, she is also the creator of Birthright, a podcast that centers joyful and healing
13 Black birth stories to reclaim the narrative of Black maternal experiences and offer a
14 counterbalance to the often-negative statistics reported in mainstream media; and
