15 WHEREAS, through her work with Irth and Birthright, Kimberly Seals Allers continues to
16 pioneer innovative tools and storytelling initiatives that uplift communities and promote
17 respectful, equitable maternity and infant care; and
18 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that this remarkable individual be
19 appropriately honored during this special time.
20 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
21 the members of this body commend Kimberly Seals Allers for her groundbreaking
22 contributions to maternal and infant health equity, recognize April 11, 2025, as Irth Day, and
23 extend best wishes for continued success.
24 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
25 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
26 Kimberly Seals Allers.
